COVE-4 Spinning wheel when building timeline and map

In js/entity_browser.media_selection.js line 38, the CSS attribute selector
built for parent.document.querySelector interpolates the DXPR instance uuid
without quotes:

    `input.dxpr-builder-image-input[data-uuid*=${instance}]`

The uuid is a hex string (0-9a-f). When it starts with a digit (~62% of
cases), the resulting selector like [data-uuid*=8e01...] is invalid per CSS
spec (an identifier cannot start with a digit). The browser raises a
DOMException which is not caught, so the rest of the function — including
the code that closes the media modal (lines 99-100) — never runs. The
modal stays open with an endlessly spinning wheel.

Fix: quote the interpolated value so any hex string is a valid string
literal for the attribute selector.

Verified: same buggy line is present in dxpr_builder 2.7.5 (installed),
2.8.x and 3.0.x on drupal.org. Upstream has never fixed it.

diff --git a/js/entity_browser.media_selection.js b/js/entity_browser.media_selection.js
--- a/js/entity_browser.media_selection.js
+++ b/js/entity_browser.media_selection.js
@@ -35,7 +35,7 @@
   // input, this ensures we don't muck up an EB selection for some FAPI widget
   const { parent } = window;
   const input = parent.document.querySelector(
-    `input.dxpr-builder-image-input[data-uuid*=${instance}]`,
+    `input.dxpr-builder-image-input[data-uuid*="${instance}"]`,
   );

   if (input) {
